datasets.name: 5461f5ea
datasets.query:
WITH LatestCompleteness AS (
    SELECT 
        *, 
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY table_name ORDER BY evaluated_at DESC) AS rn,
        CASE 
            WHEN status = 'Healthy' THEN 'Complete'
            WHEN status = 'Unhealthy' THEN 'Incomplete'
            WHEN status = 'Unknown' THEN 'Unknown'
        END AS converted_status,
        TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['daily_row_count']['actual_value'] AS INT) AS actual_row_volume, 
        TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['daily_row_count']['expectation_threshold'] AS INT) AS predicted_row_volume_threshold
    FROM identifier(:logging_table)
    WHERE quality_check_type = 'Completeness'
)
SELECT 
    catalog, 
    schema, 
    table_name,
    evaluated_at,
    status,
    converted_status,
    quality_check_type,
    actual_row_volume,
    predicted_row_volume_threshold, 
    error_message, 
    downstream_impact,
    downstream_impact.impact_level as downstream_impact_severity, 
    downstream_impact.num_downstream_tables as num_downstream_tables_impacted, 
    downstream_impact.num_queries_on_affected_tables as num_queries_impacted
FROM LatestCompleteness
WHERE rn = 1
ORDER BY evaluated_at DESC;

WITH LatestEval AS (
  SELECT 
        *,
      CASE 
            WHEN status = 'Healthy' THEN 'Complete'
            WHEN status = 'Unhealthy' THEN 'Incomplete'

)

    status,
    converted_status,

    predicted_row_volume_threshold,

    downstream_impact.num_downstream_tables as num_downstream_tables_impacted, 
    downstream_impact.num_queries_on_affected_tables as num_queries_impacted
FROM LatestEval
WHERE rn = 1
ORDER BY evaluated_at DESC;

SELECT 
    catalog, 
    schema, 
    table_name,
    evaluated_at,
    status,
    CASE 
        WHEN status = 'Fresh' THEN 'Healthy'
        WHEN status = 'Stale' THEN 'Unhealthy'
        ELSE status
    END AS converted_status,
    COALESCE(error_message, '') as error_message,
    -- hours since last update
    TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['commit_staleness']['actual_value_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600 AS hours_since_last_update, 
    -- predicted threshold for hours since last update
    TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['commit_staleness']['expectation_threshold_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600 AS predicted_update_threshold,
    TIMESTAMPADD(HOUR, - (TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['commit_staleness']['actual_value_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600), evaluated_at) AS last_data_update_timestamp, 
    TIMESTAMPADD(HOUR, - (TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['commit_staleness']['expectation_threshold_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600), evaluated_at) AS predicted_update_threshold_timestamp, 
        -- Replace NULLs with empty strings
    COALESCE(CAST(TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['event_staleness']['actual_value_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600 AS STRING), '') AS actual_latency_hours,
    COALESCE(CAST(TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['event_staleness']['expectation_threshold_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600 AS STRING), '') AS predicted_latency_threshold,
    TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['event_staleness']['actual_value_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600 AS actual_latency_hours_unformatted,
    TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['event_staleness']['expectation_threshold_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600 AS predicted_latency_threshold_unformatted,
    COALESCE(
        CAST(
            TIMESTAMPADD(
                HOUR, 
                - (TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['event_staleness']['actual_value_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600), 
                evaluated_at
            ) AS STRING
        ), ''
    ) AS last_event_timestamp,

    COALESCE(
        CAST(
            TIMESTAMPADD(
                HOUR, 
                - (TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['event_staleness']['expectation_threshold_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600), 
                evaluated_at
            ) AS STRING
        ), ''
    ) AS predicted_event_timestamp
FROM IDENTIFIER(:logging_table)
WHERE 
    evaluated_at BETWEEN :evaluated_time.min AND :evaluated_time.max
    AND table_name = :table_name
    AND quality_check_type = 'Freshness'
ORDER BY evaluated_at DESC;

datasets.name: 0edc79ec
datasets.query:
WITH LatestChecks AS (
    SELECT 
        CONCAT(catalog, ".", schema, ".", table_name) as full_table_name,
        evaluated_at,
        quality_check_type as check_type,
        status,
        table_lineage_link,
        -- Converted status based on type
        CASE 
            WHEN quality_check_type = 'Freshness' AND status = 'Fresh' THEN 'Healthy'
            WHEN quality_check_type = 'Freshness' AND status = 'Stale' THEN 'Unhealthy'
            ELSE status
        END AS converted_status,

        -- Completeness-specific fields
        TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['daily_row_count']['actual_value'] AS INT) AS actual_row_volume, 
        TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['daily_row_count']['expectation_threshold'] AS INT) AS predicted_row_volume_threshold,

        -- Freshness-specific fields
        TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['commit_staleness']['actual_value_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600 AS last_update,
        TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['commit_staleness']['expectation_threshold_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600 AS predicted_update_threshold,
        TIMESTAMPADD(
            HOUR,
            - (TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['commit_staleness']['actual_value_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600),
            evaluated_at
        ) AS last_data_update_timestamp,
        TIMESTAMPADD(
            HOUR,
            - (TRY_CAST(additional_debug_info['commit_staleness']['expectation_threshold_seconds'] AS INT) / 3600),
            evaluated_at
        ) AS predicted_update_timestamp,

        COALESCE(error_message, '') AS error_message,
        downstream_impact,
        COALESCE(CAST(downstream_impact.impact_level AS STRING), '') AS downstream_impact_severity,
        COALESCE(CAST(downstream_impact.num_downstream_tables AS STRING), '') AS num_downstream_tables_impacted,
        COALESCE(CAST(downstream_impact.num_queries_on_affected_tables AS STRING), '') AS num_queries_impacted, 

        -- Sorting helpers
        CASE 
            WHEN status = 'Unhealthy' THEN 1
            WHEN status = 'Healthy' THEN 2
            WHEN status = 'Unknown' THEN 3
            ELSE 4
        END AS status_sort_order,

        CASE 
            WHEN downstream_impact.impact_level = 4 THEN 'Very High'
            WHEN downstream_impact.impact_level = 3 THEN 'High'
            WHEN downstream_impact.impact_level = 2 THEN 'Medium'
            WHEN downstream_impact.impact_level = 1 THEN 'Low'
            ELSE ""
        END AS downstream_impact_severity_label,
        -- Human-readable reason
        CASE 
            WHEN quality_check_type = 'Freshness' AND status = 'Unhealthy' THEN 
                CONCAT(
                    'The table was predicted to be updated by ', 
                    CAST(predicted_update_timestamp AS STRING), 
                    ', but the last update was at ', 
                    CAST(last_data_update_timestamp AS STRING)
                )
            WHEN quality_check_type = 'Completeness' AND status = 'Unhealthy' THEN 
                CONCAT(
                    'At least ',
                    predicted_row_volume_threshold, 
                    ' rows were predicted to be affected in the last 24 hours, but only ', 
                    actual_row_volume, 
                    ' rows were affected.'
                )
            WHEN converted_status = 'Unknown' THEN error_message
            ELSE ""
        END AS reason,

        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY table_name, quality_check_type 
            ORDER BY evaluated_at DESC
        ) AS rn
    FROM IDENTIFIER(:`logging_table`)
    WHERE quality_check_type IN ('Completeness', 'Freshness')
      AND (table_name = :table_name OR :table_name = 'All tables')
      AND (catalog = :catalog OR :catalog = 'All catalogs')
      AND (schema = :schema OR :schema = 'All schemas')
)
SELECT 
    evaluated_at, 
    full_table_name as table_name, 
    check_type, 
    converted_status as status, 
    downstream_impact_severity_label, 
    num_queries_impacted, 
    num_downstream_tables_impacted, 
    reason,
    table_lineage_link
FROM LatestChecks
WHERE rn = 1
  AND (check_type = :quality_check_type OR :quality_check_type = 'All checks')
  AND (status = :status OR :status = 'All statuses')
ORDER BY 
  status_sort_order ASC,  -- Unhealthy first
  downstream_impact.impact_level DESC,  -- Highest impact first
  evaluated_at DESC;

datasets.name: 0883446b
datasets.query:
WITH LatestDailyCheck AS (
    SELECT
        catalog,
        schema,
        table_name,
        quality_check_type,
        status,
        CAST(evaluated_at AS DATE) AS evaluation_date,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY CAST(evaluated_at AS DATE), table_name, quality_check_type
            ORDER BY evaluated_at DESC
        ) AS rn
    FROM IDENTIFIER(:`logging_table`)
    WHERE quality_check_type IN ('Completeness', 'Freshness')
)
, DailyAggregates AS (
    SELECT
        evaluation_date,
        quality_check_type,
        COUNT(*) AS total_tables,
        COUNT_IF(status = 'Healthy') AS healthy_tables
    FROM LatestDailyCheck
    WHERE rn = 1
    GROUP BY evaluation_date, quality_check_type
)
SELECT
    evaluation_date,
    quality_check_type,
    healthy_tables,
    total_tables,
    ROUND(100.0 * healthy_tables / total_tables, 2) AS percent_healthy
FROM DailyAggregates
ORDER BY evaluation_date, quality_check_type;

datasets.name: 6a0f2ffc
datasets.query:
WITH LatestFreshness AS (
    SELECT * FROM (
        SELECT 
            *, 
            ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY table_name ORDER BY evaluated_at DESC) AS rn,
            DATE(evaluated_at) AS eval_date,
            CASE 
                WHEN status = 'Fresh' THEN 'Healthy'
                WHEN status = 'Stale' THEN 'Unhealthy'
                ELSE status
            END AS converted_status
        FROM IDENTIFIER(:logging_table)
        WHERE quality_check_type = 'Freshness'
    ) subquery
    WHERE rn = 1
),
LatestCompleteness AS (
    SELECT * FROM (
        SELECT 
            *, 
            ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY table_name ORDER BY evaluated_at DESC) AS rn,
            DATE(evaluated_at) AS eval_date,
            status AS converted_status
        FROM IDENTIFIER(:logging_table)
        WHERE quality_check_type = 'Completeness'
    ) subquery
    WHERE rn = 1
),
CombinedStatus AS (
    SELECT 
        COALESCE(f.table_name, c.table_name) AS table_name,
        f.evaluated_at AS freshness_evaluated_at,
        c.evaluated_at AS completeness_evaluated_at,
        f.eval_date AS eval_date,
        f.converted_status AS freshness_status,
        c.converted_status AS completeness_status,
        CASE 
            WHEN f.converted_status = 'Unhealthy' OR c.converted_status = 'Unhealthy' THEN 'Unhealthy'
            WHEN f.converted_status = 'Unknown' OR c.converted_status = 'Unknown' THEN 'Unknown'
            WHEN f.converted_status IS NULL THEN c.converted_status
            WHEN c.converted_status IS NULL THEN f.converted_status
            ELSE 'Healthy'
        END AS final_status

    FROM LatestFreshness f
    FULL OUTER JOIN LatestCompleteness c 
        ON f.table_name = c.table_name
    AND f.eval_date = c.eval_date
),
statuses AS (
    SELECT 'Healthy' AS status UNION ALL
    SELECT 'Unhealthy' UNION ALL
    SELECT 'Unknown'
)
SELECT 
    s.status, 
    COALESCE(c.count, 0) AS count,
    ROUND(COALESCE(c.count, 0) / (SELECT Count(*) FROM CombinedStatus), 4) AS percentage
FROM statuses s
LEFT JOIN (
    SELECT
        final_status AS status,
        COUNT(*) AS count
    FROM CombinedStatus
    GROUP BY final_status
) c ON s.status = c.status;

            WHEN status = 'Unhealthy' THEN 1
            WHEN status = 'Healthy' THEN 2
            WHEN status = 'Unknown' THEN 3
            ELSE 4
        END AS status_sort_order,

        CASE 
            WHEN downstream_impact.impact_level = 4 THEN 'Very High'
            WHEN downstream_impact.impact_level = 3 THEN 'High'
            WHEN downstream_impact.impact_level = 2 THEN 'Medium'
            WHEN downstream_impact.impact_level = 1 THEN 'Low'
            ELSE ""
        END AS downstream_impact_severity_label,
        -- Human-readable reason
        CASE 
            WHEN quality_check_type = 'Freshness' AND status = 'Unhealthy' THEN 
                CONCAT(
                    'The table was predicted to be updated by ', 
                    CAST(predicted_update_timestamp AS STRING), 
                    ', but the last update was at ', 
                    CAST(last_data_update_timestamp AS STRING)
                )
            WHEN quality_check_type = 'Completeness' AND status = 'Unhealthy' THEN 
                CONCAT(
                    'The last update to the table was predicted to affect at least ', 
                    predicted_row_volume_threshold, 
                    ' rows, but it only affected ', 
                    actual_row_volume, 
                    ' rows'
                )
            ELSE ""
        END AS reason,

        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY table_name, quality_check_type 
            ORDER BY evaluated_at DESC
        ) AS rn
    FROM IDENTIFIER(:`logging_table`)
    WHERE quality_check_type IN ('Completeness', 'Freshness')
      AND (table_name = :table_name OR :table_name = 'All tables')
      AND (catalog = :catalog OR :catalog = 'All catalogs')
      AND (schema = :schema OR :schema = 'All schemas')
)
SELECT evaluated_at, full_table_name as table_name, last_data_update_timestamp
FROM LatestChecks
WHERE rn = 1
  AND is_static = 'true' 
ORDER BY 
  last_data_update_timestamp ASC, 
  evaluated_at DESC;

widget.textbox_spec:
## How to use this dashboard
There are two tabs: `Quality Overview` (the current tab) and `Table Quality Details`
- `Quality Overview` provides a holistic view of the latest data quality across all tables.
-  `Table Quality Details` shows why a specific table is marked as healthy or unhealthy.

widget.name: fe7f94e9
widget.textbox_spec:
## Schema Overview
Understand the latest data quality across all tables in your schema(s).
- A table is  "Healthy" if it passes all quality checks.
- A table is  "Unhealthy" if it fails any quality check.
- A table is  "Unknown" if any quality check is Unknown.

## Static Tables List

widget.name: fc14a50b
widget.textbox_spec:
## Freshness
Monitors how recently a table has been updated. This table is considered fresh when the the last update falls below the predicted threshold.

widget.name: 0bfe5fc9
widget.textbox_spec:
## Completeness
Monitors a table's row volume. This table is considered complete if the row volume in the last 24 hours is above the predicted threshold.

## Data Latency
Shows how recently events have arrived in the table.\
This section will be empty if no timestamp column has been specified. Details on Data Latency monitoring can be found [here.](https://docs.databricks.com/gcp/en/lakehouse-monitoring/anomaly-detection#customize-freshness-and-completeness-evaluations)
